Did some preliminary hacking on my end, just to see what's what:

```
sevagh:alacritty $ git diff src/main.rs
diff --git a/src/main.rs b/src/main.rs
index 0888c9b..3480ac6 100644
--- a/src/main.rs
+++ b/src/main.rs
@@ -25,6 +25,10 @@ extern crate log;
 #[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
 extern crate dirs;

+extern crate gio;
+extern crate gtk;
+extern crate glib;
+
 use std::error::Error;
 use std::sync::Arc;
 #[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
@@ -114,6 +118,12 @@ fn run(mut config: Config, options: &cli::Options) -> Result<(), Box<Error>> {
     let terminal = Term::new(&config, display.size().to_owned());
     let terminal = Arc::new(FairMutex::new(terminal));

+    let app_name = "com.github.jwilm.alacritty"; //needs to be in this form to be a valid GTK id
+    // Set the Application Name to play nicely with .desktop files in Wayland
+    gtk::Application::new(app_name, gio::ApplicationFlags::FLAGS_NONE);
+    glib::set_application_name("Alacritty");
+    glib::set_prgname(Some(app_name));
```

This is based on observing the Python source code of some other application.

Anyway, it didn't actually work yet - not sure what I'm missing.

Also, I'm not sure if this belongs better in one of alacritty's dependencies (winit, glutin, etc.).
